items.name: Object_Live2DCharacter
items.content:
# ===================================================================
#
#   Script: Object_Live2DCharacter
#
#   $$COPYRIGHT$$
#
# ===================================================================
class Object_Live2DCharacter extends gs.Object_Visual
    @objectCodecBlackList = ["parent"]
    
    ###*
    * A game object for an animated Live2D visual novel character. 
    *
    * @module gs
    * @class Object_Live2DCharacter
    * @extends gs.Object_Visual
    * @memberof gs
    * @constructor
    ###
    constructor: (record, data) ->
        super(data)
        @zIndex = 200
        
        ###*
        * The ID of the character-record used.
        * @property rid
        * @type number
        ###
        @rid = data?.id || (record?.index ? -1)
        
        ###*
        * The rotation-angle of the character in degrees. The rotation center depends on the
        * anchor-point.
        * @property angle
        * @type number
        ###
        @angle = 0
        
        ###*
        * The color tone of the object used for the visual presentation.
        * @property tone
        * @type gs.Tone
        ###
        @tone = new Tone(0, 0, 0, 0)
        
        ###*
        * The color of the object used for the visual presentation.
        * @property color
        * @type gs.Color
        ###
        @color = new Color(255, 255, 255, 0)
        
        ###*
        * The Live2D model used for the visual presentation.
        * @property model
        * @type gs.Live2DModel
        ###
        @model = if data? then ResourceManager.getLive2DModel("Live2D/#{data.modelName}") else null
        
        ###*
        * The resource name of a Live2D model used for the visual presentation.
        * @property modelName
        * @type string
        ###
        @modelName = data?.modelName
        
        ###*
        * The Live2D motion.
        * @property motion
        * @type gs.Live2DMotion
        ###
        @motion = data?.motion || name: "", loop: yes
        
        ###*
        * The Live2D motion group.
        * @property motion
        * @type gs.Live2DMotionGroup
        ###
        @motionGroup = data?.motionGroup
        
        ###*
        * The Live2D expression.
        * @property expression
        * @type gs.Live2DExpression
        ###
        @expression = data?.expression || name: "" #RecordManager.characterExpressions[data?.expressionId || 0]
        
        ###*
        * The character's behavior component which contains the character-specific logic.
        * @property behavior
        * @type vn.Component_CharacterBehavior
        ###
        @behavior = new vn.Component_CharacterBehavior()
        @logic = @behavior
        
        ###*
        * The object's animator-component to execute different kind of animations like move, rotate, etc. on it.
        * @property animator
        * @type vn.Component_Animator
        ###
        @animator = new gs.Component_Animator()
        
        ###*
        * The object's visual-component to display the game object on screen.
        * @property visual
        * @type gs.Component_Sprite
        ###
        @visual = new gs.Component_Live2D()
        @visual.modelFolder = "Live2D"
        
        @addComponent(@logic)
        @addComponent(@animator)
        @addComponent(@visual)
      
    ###*
    * Serializes the object into a data-bundle.
    *
    * @method toDataBundle
    * @return {Object} The data-bundle.
    ###    
    toDataBundle: -> 
        rid: @rid, 
        x: @dstRect.x, 
        y: @dstRect.y, 
        opacity: @opacity,
        offset: @offset,
        zoom: @zoom,
        origin: @origin,
        mirror: @mirror, 
        expression: @expression, 
        modelName: @modelName,
        motion: @motion,
        motionGroup: @motionGroup,
        expression: @expression
        
        

vn.Object_Live2DCharacter = Object_Live2DCharacter
